39. mendaci lyra, parallel to v, 20. He must lie to praise her, but he will lie if she pleases. Orelli thinks that it is an equivoque, and that she might‘have taken ‘mendaci’ to mean ‘which lied xbefore in reviling you ' 3 but the other meaning of the words would have been the more obvious of the two.
